Bro that’s the issue: your API is running fine, but the mobile app points to:

```text
http://127.0.0.1:5117/
```

On your Android phone, `127.0.0.1` means the phone itself. Last night it worked because you probably had `adb reverse` active. Today it was gone.

I already ran this for you:

```powershell
& "C:\Program Files (x86)\Android\android-sdk\platform-tools\adb.exe" reverse tcp:5117 tcp:5117
```

Now your phone’s `127.0.0.1:5117` forwards to your laptop API.

Every time you reconnect/run mobile, do this order:

1. Start API:

```powershell
cd "C:\Users\ASUS VIVOBOOK\OneDrive\Documents\Repository\EEMOCantilanSDS\EEMOCantilanSDS.Api"
